claim.claim-text:
A display device for lighting objects, comprising:
a frame (10) having an opening at a back side thereof, a permeable vision window (11) at a middle of front side thereof, and a base (12) and a projection light (13) at a bottom of inner side thereof;
a film-coated glass (20) mounted on the vision window (11), having a front side with light transmittancy facing toward an external part of the vision window (11) and a reverse side with reflectivity;
a support bracket (30) arranged in the frame (10) and having at least one positioning hole (33) thereon;
a transparent bottle (40) being able to emit light effect, corresponding to a height of the vision window (11) arranged in the positioning holes (33), having a bottom (41) on a top of the projection light (13), and filled with a filler (43) with liquid;
a first reflection mirror (50A) and a second refection mirror (50B) fixed on the support bracket (30), located at a rear side of the transparent bottle (40), and having reflection surfaces facing forward and a center serving as a reference to define the first and second symmetrical reflection mirrors (50A), (50B), and both sides of the first and second reflection mirrors (50A), (50B) inclined forward to form an angle (θ) being not parallel with the film-coated glass (20) with 180° angle but between 145 ° and 175 °; after the filler (43) of the transparent bottle (40) is reflected repeatedly and cumulatively by the first and second reflection mirrors (50A), (50B), the vision window (11) shows shapes in an inward serial arrangement from the middle to the unlimited extension and diffusion at both sides thereof; and
a cover plate (60) arranged at the back opening of the frame (10).
